# A program that converts a temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit:
#
# Prompt the user for a Temperature in Celsius
celsius = float(input("Enter a temerature in Celsius: "))
#
# Convert the temperature to Fahrenheit
fahrenheit = (celsius * 9 / 5) + 32
#
# Print the result
#
print(f"{celsius}°C is the equivalent to {fahrenheit}°F.")
#
# Do you see that "f" fucntion again .... look at its usage here.  It is the same
